foods.name: Grilled Shrimp on the Barbie
foods.description: Seasoned with a special blend of herbs and spices then flame grilled. Served with Outback’s own garlic toast and classic rémoulade sauce.
review: We ordered these for the table and they were a hit!

foods.name: Sydney Shrooms
foods.description: Lightly battered and fried mushrooms served with house-made ranch dressing.

foods.name: Aussie Twisted Ribs
foods.description: Our tender Baby Back Ribs fried Outback-style then tossed in tangy BBQ sauce and drizzled with our spicy signature bloom sauce. Garnished with spicy house-made pickles.

foods.name: Seared Pepper Ahi*
foods.description: Seared rare with garlic pepper seasoning. Served with a creamy ginger soy sauce and wasabi.

foods.name: Gold Coast Coconut Shrimp**
foods.description: Hand-dipped in batter, rolled in coconut and fried golden. Paired with Creole marmalade.

foods.name: Steakhouse Mac & Cheese Bites
foods.description: Eight golden bites filled with macaroni, Asiago, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese. Served with house-made ranch dressing.

foods.name: Three Cheese Steak Dip
foods.description: Blend of steak, Gouda, Parmesan and Jack cheeses, red bell peppers and onions. Served with tortilla chips for dipping.

reviews.review: Haven't had one bad experience. Always great food and great service. Not too expensive either. Definitely will be returning.
Definitely a great place to get a quick bite or sit down with your friends!

I come to this establishment frequently. One of my favorite places to go. I usually sit at the bar and order my prime rib and watch the games going on. Bartender is great. She always welcomes me with my favorite drink. Prices are reasonable.
